Part of my post from June 12th 2006: -
for some reason, before i was in a relationship, i gave awesome advice. i'm not sure if i would anymore, cos i can actually imagine how it would feel now. like before, i said if a guy ever cheated on me, that would be it, i'd leave. but now i imagine if anthony did that to me, i know i'd probably find every excuse for him and try my best to stay with him. maybe i'm pathetic and dependant, or i just know that he would never do that to me so its not quite real.

I OBVIOUSLY LOST THAT BET
but it's funny cos i did try to find every excuse
then realised he's just a cunt who couldn't keep it in his pants
and chose the fugliest bogan of a chick to put it in
and that's not even the "woman scorned" in me talking
everyone who knows her who i told was the other woman were sort of dumbfounded for a few seconds
she's not good
and she's pregnant
but this is a bitchfest for another time
if you wish for details, feel free to make requests

honestly, this break up was so freaking dramatic
but then again, most things i do tend to be a bit OTT
but now i've gotten myself all fired up
so current news on the Fucktard is below, read at own will

seriously want to kick him in the face
if i was Chuck Norris, the rapidness of the roundhouse kicks i would be doing would shatter the time space continum
thats how much i am pissed at him this week

i have a few bit of his stuff still - i've had it all packed up and ready to go for months
keep in mind, we broke up on the 1st of August, so it's been over FIVE MONTHS
actually, it'd be our 3 year anniversay on tuesday if we were still together
i realised this earlier - bit random, not sure why my brain told me this when i was looking at the calendar

anyways
he keeps messaging me at random times saying "oh, i found more of your books in my wardrobe"
i'm like "that's nice fucktard, put it with the others and lets get this shit over with"
apparently i've lefts like multiple garbage bags worth of stuff at his parent's place
considering i've been to his house and collected bags worth of stuff already i have no idea how this can be true
but regardless, he says he has it and i want his shit out of my house also so an exchange needs to be made

but he's being a little bitch, isn't he
i think he still hopes there's a chance we're getting back together
and seriously, there's not even a shred of hope for that
i've got someone else on the brain and considering the whole time we were dating i barely found other guys to be attractive [haha how fucking loyal am I cos Anthony's not what you'd describe as "a looker" - Ren nicknamed him "sleazy Italian" so work off that mental picture - I just get the Rose Coloured Glasses effect cos I'm tard/loyal as fuck], having someone on the brain is like as official as i can be

but anyways
i sms'd him on wednesday saying i'm sick of waiting for him to organise himself, bring my shit over at 1pm and pick up ur crap today
he messaged back with "don't give me that crap, you know i've been waiting for you"
and then 30 minutes later "btw, i'll be out at a pool gathering that time anyways"
like seriously, do i care that you're going swimming?
NO ARSEHOLE SHOW UP LATE AND GET OUT OF MY LIFE
and the whole waiting for me thing is bullshit cos i spoke to him on like thursday when he sent me one of his random "oh, i found more of your books in my wardrobe" messages over msn and said he thinks there's more in there
so he's obviously not ready to do the swap cos he hasn't finished getting my shit together
it fired me up good and proper, despite how much i didn't want him to effect me
i had to turn my phone off cos i knew if i replied it would go on for hours and i seriously have too much work to do to be playing his games like that

he still wants to be friends
i told him to go fuck himself
every so often he asks whether there's still no chance for us to be friends
and every time he asks
there's even less

i want him out of my life properly
we don't share mutual friends and the few that we did either see him or see me now
his friends never really liked me so i'm not really losing anything there
Leah was dating his best friend but they broke up and she's in London so I don't even speak to him
I met Anthony through Tim - i haven't been out with tim pretty much since we broke up and really, i don't want to - he really needs a girlfriend, he's getting very scary-creepy
It should be so eas to just have him no longer exist to me
And for a good few months, it was like dropped off the face of the earth
And i was damn happy about that
So i am really unimpressed with his current attitute
And i don't want anything that has potential to happen with someone else to be effected by the fact that Anthony is being so childish
Cos i really would like it to happen - not sure if the person i'm thinking of is feeling the same way, but i will find out eventually - possibly sooner if they are reading this!
Anthony is making me feel like I look like I'm not over him, it's like he's sensed that I'm moved on and happy with where i am in the world at the moment and doing things for myself again and is trying to keep himself in my mind and ruin it all
And it's unfortantly working, but not in a good way for him
The Motherfucker.

I had a pretty rad weekend
yeah, RAD, I can't remember the last time when "rad" was my describing word of choice, without sounding like a douche
but today it is and this weekend was :)

i started to do it seriously on november 16th, 
have set promises to myself
what i will reward myself with
going to the gym at least three times a week
trying to eat better 
and all that
i'm going to get a rose vine tattoo or something like that and for every 5kilos i lose, i am going to get a rose bud added
milestones anyone?
and by getting it tattooed, it means i am not allowed to even THINK of putting it back on
otherwise i end up with a meaningless tattoo and a giant reminder of how little self-control and determination i have
which isn't very fun
this morning i weighted myself
current loss to date: 5.9
someone call the tattooist!
excuse me while I wet myself with joy.
it's just a little bit exciting.
so pleased/proud of myself

i'm having the best talk to lisa on msn about anthony and love and stuff. i really need lisa, she's only only person i feel ok about telling her about these things. i'm not a big talker, well, not about the genuine things about me. i talk about things a lot but i don't really talk about things. when it comes to like the real parts that make up someone, i'd rather be the informed then the informer. i guess it comes down to being scared that they'll go "thats really not normal" or not want to hear about it, cos theres even things that i think about saying and i go "don't say that, its scary/too intense" cos i do have what i call "scary love" in me. i'm not sure. and i'm sure its part knowing what its like hearing about your friend whos absolutely smitten, and you yourself have no one. she told me i was making her envious, usually this would make me drop the wall and stop, but she had an awesome eight month relationship with someone and when they broke up, i was there for her and when they were together, i would listen to her talking about how great he was.
i've done that for a few friends, been the one that they talk to about how their heart is going, whether it be because i can see that they have the hots for someone, or because they're in a relationship and need advice. for some reason, before i was in a relationship, i gave awesome advice. i'm not sure if i would anymore, cos i can actually imagine how it would feel now. like before, i said if a guy ever cheated on me, that would be it, i'd leave. but now i imagine if anthony did that to me, i know i'd probably find every excuse for him and try my best to stay with him. maybe i'm pathetic and dependant, or i just know that he would never do that to me so its not quite real.
he's not what i expected. i told him that today. he didn't understand, and i can understand that. he's so much better then the type of guy i thought i'd end up with. maybe it was just my self-worth running on empty, but whatever it was, he's the opposite of everything and i wished i believed in god so i could thank him for it.

i'm so fucking angry that i feel like crying and i don't even really know why

actually, yes i do, it because for some reason two of the men in my life suddenly seem to see me as an ATM

anthony and i have been going out for four months and so far he owes me $155 and thats just for concert tickets, if i actually added up the times i've paid for dinner or the movie or whatever, i'm sure it would have cleared 200. he can't pay me back because he doesn't work full time cos of TAFE and he owes money to his mother as well and she seems to be more intent on nagging him about it then i am, and somehow every time i go to ask anthony about when i'm going to get some of my money back, he brings it up before me saying how he wants to give me some of the money and i end up feeling bad cos i know that if i make me him give some of the money it'll mean he'll be broke for a week and i'd probably end up lending him money for the week anyways. i feel like he's my child and i have to pay for his food and schooling and shit. but i can't say any of this to his face cos its mean and i don't want to be mean to him 

next is my brother. chris has been unemployed for a few months now i think. i dunno, it feels like forever. he's on the dole but like he said today "i got the government money yesterday, but that's gone" this is like at 1 in the afternoon the day after he got it. he's a fuckwit. we went "halves" in a mothers day present this year and i even had to CHOOSE AND BUY a card from him to mum. and she liked his better, because i chose one which was a little mean to chris, but fucking true cos he owes her more money then i want to know because it upsets me. so its friday night and chris wants to go out (i have to work tomorrow morning hoo-fucking-ray) so he asked me when i came home for lunch if he could borrow eighty bucks, which i didn't really want to lend him cos i know HE can't pay me back so it would end up come back to me from mum. but i was like, if i remember on my way home i'll get some $80 out from the bank for you, and he's like "ok, if you forget, doesn't matter". but i didn't remember and we ran into each other in the driveway as i'm coming home from work and he's like "did you get the $80?" and i tell him i've forgotten but he tells me, thats ok, i was going to ask for a hundred. so not only have i not gotten home yet, come all the way home when the ATM is LITERALLY three stores down from my work, and not only does he want another 20 bucks, but he's been sitting around at home all day and decided to not call me and leave a message on my mobile which would have meant i'd have remembered before i'd gotten home like a nice person would, but to wait til i'm completely knackered, almost home, busting for a pee, to meet me six foot from the front door to tell me to turn around and get him more money then i was originally. AND NOW HE'S MADE ME FEEL MEAN FOR BEING COMPLETELY FUCKING SHITTED OFF ABOUT IT. he does this every fucking time. i mean, i have the money yeah, but i work for it. he does nothing and is like.. surprised? ... that he can't afford to go out on friday nights? 

its all just not fair. 

but maybe this is all just a cover up for me not coping with nana dying very well and now everyone i care about treating me crappily.

but maybe i'm too sensitive.

but maybe absolutely no one will read this and emphasise how little anyone cares.

i'm going to go have a cry now, have a good weekend.

there watching the phone play all the way through cos it was just so amazingly awesome i couldn't bring myself to make it stop. the battery in this phone doesn't last as long as my other one but i've probably been using this one a lot more since it takes photos and i can actually call people now without worrying it'll drop out cos i've run out of credit. at the moment i've been looking for a job. schools over, that holiday feeling is gone, now i'm just bored out of my frikkin little mindand can't afford to go anywhere cos the money i made over the christmas period is just about gone. unemployment is definately not my thing. i couldn't live off the dole and never work, i need to be productive in some way, which i find quite surprising give my high level of laziness i thought i had. if i don't get a job soon, i may have to start watching daytime tv and writing letters regarding the amount of violence in the news, especially since my computers broke at the moment. thats a scary thought. i've applied for 16 positions so far, mainly receptionist/administration jobs cos they're most likely to not need experience, of which i have very little so this works for me. i did apply for a hair dressing appreticiship though. dunno about that, but anyway. out of those 16 applications, i've gone to four interviews. i hate interviews simply because i spend half an hour trying to get myself out of bed at some rediculous hour of the morning like SEVEN AM i mean really, what am i, a school student or something, an hour dolling myself up so i can fool them into believeing i'm a responcible teenager bahaha, another hour or so getting to the damn place via public trasport cos i don't drive, in my fucking shoes which are trying to kill me, reminding myself to take out my lipring cos i forget that its there, just to sit down with the person for 10 minutes and thats the entire thing. two and a half hours for 10 minutes. its crazyness, but at least i'm finally getting some interviews. i hate how companies don't send you a "thanks. but no thanks"email or something when you apply for a position. i always worry that they haven't recieved it yet. i like emailing the person because i've found if it's done over the internet, they recieve it straight away and tend to contact you within half an hour of it being sent out. thats if they contact you at all, obviously. so far, i really don't think i'll get offered any of the jobs i've been to interviews for, they seem to want more professional, experienced receptionists. and thats fine. i would like the job at the optometrist though, they offer the job and a traineeship if the applicant is interested in it, which i mean, if i was going to be doing the work anyway, it would be a bonus to recieve a TAFE certificate III in Business [i think thats the one she said it was] at the end of twelve months to say "yeah baby, she's trained up and ready to rock and roll" when all it is extra is like homework from a trainer who'd come into your work once a week to go through all the theory and whatnot of the job with you. plus, the optometrist is seriously, about five minutes from my house, the two optometrists who own it seem nice as anything, they'd pay for the TAFE fees if i did the traineeship which employers don't have to but these people do, they pay more then most places pay award-wise, and seconds away from my favourite chicken shop, can we all say HEAVEN?? plus there'd be no having to work out transport cos i can walk. i would lovelovelove a job that i could walk to, but doesn't everyone, i mean home buisnesses are pretty popular these days lol. i would really really really like to work there, but i'm trying not to get too attachted to the idea of working at any of these places cos i'm positive they will find someone much more fitting then i am for these jobs. which sucks, but thats reality. i've been putting together my portfolio too, which has been quite nice, cos its kind of reassuring. i have all these certificates and such all in the one place to flick through and go "wow. i have actually done a fair amount of things in my life." they mighten be very high standard zOMG things like volunteer fighter fighting or anything but still, they're there and i did them. i dunno, it just perks me up a bit to see them i suppose. i'm silly like that.
